commit.message:
use isolated_build in tox.ini

The isolated_build option is required when pyproject.toml is present.
Add it to fix the following tox error:

```
ERROR: pyproject.toml file found.
To use a PEP 517 build-backend you are required to configure tox to use an isolated_build:
https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/example/package.html
```

use typing-extensions on python<3.8 only

The Protocol class is built-in in stdlib typing module since Python 3.8.
Require typing-extensions only for older Python versions, especially
that many distributions are no longer shipping Python < 3.8
and therefore this package could specifically be pulling it in on user
systems.

correct typing-extensions dependency

The Protocol class has been introduced in typing-extensions 3.6.4,
so require at least this version.
